(20, 0, 63, 'lawyer blog', 'The tussle between the Shiv Sena and cops over the release of My Name Is Khan is likely to result in Rs 40-45 cr losses.', '<p>IIMs are not producing the kind of students required by the industry. The kind of people industry today requires are those who have the competence to work under ambiguity and have the agility to cope with different dynamic situations, said Rajeev Bhadauria, president, Human Resources, Reliance ADAG.</p><br/><p>He added, Dynamism should be the primary input today in all models of education that we propose to teach. So, our curriculum must make people dynamic.</p><br/><p>He was speaking at Connexion a PGPX (Post Graduate Programme for Executives) conclave organised at IIM-A here.</p>', 1, '2010-02-11 22:45:30', '', '', '', 0),
(21, 0, 63, ' Hidden drugs in roses Cocaine in V-Day roses', 'A couple of days before Valentines Day, a consignment of cocaine was found hidden among 20,000 roses at the Amsterdam airport. ', '<p class="&quot;first&quot;" style="">A week before Valentines Day, a consignment of cocaine was found hidden among 20,000 roses from Latin America at Amsterdam airport, Dutch authorities said on Wednesday.</p><br/><p>The roses, a popular Feb. 14 Valentines Day gift, arrived last Sunday on a flight from Bogota, Colombia, which stopped over in Puerto Rico, the public prosecutors office said in a statement. The drug was found in cellophane packets hidden in boxes containing the roses.</p>', 1, '2010-02-11 23:35:51', '', '', '', 0),
(22, 15, 0, ' Mumbai to Melbourne', 'Mumbai is a long way from Melbourne but analysing the politics of the Shiv Sena is instructive to what is happening in Australia. ', '<p class="first" style="margin-top: 0pt;">That a significant number of Indian students have been assaulted and on occasion killed in Australia over recent months is an indisputable fact. But does this necessarily mean, as a large section of the media and the government of India seem to believe, that these incidents are driven by racism? Or is it simply generic urban crime as claimed by the Australians?</p><br/><p>By digging into their respective corners, both sides of the debate, particularly the Indian side, are missing a crucial analytical point that relates to the challenge of a new kind of migration from India to Australia.</p>', 1, '2010-02-11 23:37:37', '', '', '', 0),
(23, 0, 63, 'Hindu wins battle for funeral pyre in Britain', 'A devout Hindu was overjoyed after winning a court fight that will now allow open-air cremation in Britain.hi', '<p class="first" style="margin-top: 0pt;">A devout Hindu declared himself overjoyed on Wednesday after winning a court fight to be allowed to be cremated in Britain on an open-air funeral pyre.</p><br/><p>Spiritual healer Davender Ghai, 71, was granted his last wish by the Court of Appeal which ruled the controversial ceremony could be carried out without a change</p><br/><p>&nbsp;</p><br/>&nbsp;<br/><p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, '2010-02-11 23:42:41', '', '', '', 0),
(24, 15, 0, 'fsdfdsgfdfgdfg', 'Indias most eligible bachelor may not be single and available for long. This Valentines week, take a look at Rahuls love match.', '<p>Ghai believes that a pyre is essential to "a good death" and for the release of his spirit into the afterlife.</p><br/><p>&nbsp;</p><br/><p>He wants a permit for an open-air cremation site in a remote part of Northumberland in northern England.</p><br/><p>&nbsp;</p><br/><p>Ghai was originally refused permission by the local authority in Newcastle and lost a legal challenge to that decision at the High Court last</p><br/><p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, '2010-02-11 23:44:01', '', '', '', 0),
